# ISSUE-002 spike — DB connection.
#
# Use the DIRECT connection (session mode, port 5432), NOT the transaction pooler
# (port 6543). The spike sets per-transaction GUCs (`set local role authenticated`,
# `set local request.jwt.claims`, `set local hnsw.ef_search`) and needs them to
# persist within a transaction — transaction-pooler mode can break that.
#
# Supabase → Project Settings → Database → Connection string → "Direct connection".
# It looks like:
#   postgresql://postgres:<PASSWORD>@db.<ref>.supabase.co:5432/postgres
DATABASE_URL=

# Optional overrides for the corpus profile (contestable-by-design; see src/config.ts).
# N_MEMORIES=50000
# N_USERS=20
# N_ROLES=6
# ITERATIONS=200
